File Operations

When you copy, move or delete files, Midnight Commander shows the file operations dialog. It shows the files currently being processed and uses up to two progress bars. The file bytes bar indicates the percentage of the current file that has been processed so far. The total bytes bar indicates the percentage of the total size of the tagged files that has been handled. Counters that show how many of the tagged files have been handled are displayed. If the Verbose option is off, the file bytes bar and total bytes bar are not shown.

